review_blob: Very dark, with a slightly smoky, chocolate aroma to it.  A bitter taste, one of the better Michelob's I have had.
Wasn't really sure what I was in for, but was pleasantly suprised.  Slight orange smell, and a hint of citrus made for a decent beer overall.
Virtually no taste, but the slight hint of one that is there isn't terribly pleasant.  I would drink it if it was free, but I'd rather buy a bottle of water.
Not hard to drink, and you can get it everwhere.  A staple of college alcoholics.
Smooth, but lacked any pronounced flavor.  Bittersweet finish was nice though.
If you only have four dollars and you wallet and you are going for sheer volume of consumption, I guess this is your best bet.
